<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-03-02T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-03-02T21:00:00-05:00" n="283" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d283">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.00/1134.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-03T10:00:00+08:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 3, 1912—10 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The 200 American troops have arrived. Serious mutiny, with looting and
                            burning, at Tientsin last night.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Calhoun.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>